  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἔστησαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 1:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐνώπιον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", see above.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καὶ προσευξάμενοι ἐπέθηκαν αὐτοῖς τὰς χεῖρας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": change of subject. This is the first mention of the laying on of hands in the Apostolic Church. No doubt the practice was customary in the Jewish Church, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 27:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 34:9",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; see also Edersheim, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jewish Social Life",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 281, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Jesus the Messiah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ii., 382, and Hamburger, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Real-Encyclopädie",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ii., 6, pp. 882–886, “Ordinirung, Ordination”; Hort, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Ecclesia",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", p. 216; Gore, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Church and the Ministry",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", pp. 187, 382; but the constant practice of it by our Lord Himself was sufficient to recommend it to His Apostles. It soon became the outward and visible sign of the bestowal of spiritual gifts in the Apostolic Church, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 4:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 5:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and every convert was instructed in its meaning as one of the elementary teachings of the faith, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Hebrews 6:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". That the act was a means of grace is evident from St. Paul’s words, for he reminds Timothy of the grace thus bestowed upon him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Timothy 4:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Timothy 1:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and from the narrative of St. Luke in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and passages below. But that it was not a mere outward act dissociated from prayer is evident from St. Luke’s words in the passage before us, in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". See especially Hooker, v., lxvi., 1, 2; see below in 8 and 13, and Gore, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Church and the Ministry",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", especially note G. Holtzmann would draw a distinction between the laying on of hands here and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 8:17",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Here, he contends, it only corresponds to the customary usage at the ordination of a Rabbi, as the Seven had already received the Holy Ghost, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "cf.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 13:1",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". But ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 6:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " undoubtedly justifies us in believing that an accession of power was granted after the laying on of hands, and now for the first time mention is made of St. Stephen’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "τέρατα καὶ σημεῖα μεγάλα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (see St. Chrysostom’s comment).",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
